Configured a security group within AWS to permit inbound traffic on port 22 (SSH) for secure remote access and port 80 (HTTP) to enable web traffic.
2. Server Setup and Configuration:

Established an SSH connection to the newly launched EC2 instance.
Updated the system's package lists and upgraded existing packages to their latest versions using apt update and apt upgrade -y.
Installed the Apache2 web server using apt install apache2.
Started and enabled the Apache2 service to run automatically on system boot using systemctl start apache2 and systemctl enable apache2.
3. Project Deployment:

