Created a project directory within the server's document root: sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/your_project_name.
Transferred the HTML file to the server using scp or another secure file transfer method.
Cloned the project's Git repository to the server using sudo -u www-data git clone git@github.com:your_username/your_repository_name.git /var/www/html/your_project_name.
4. Apache Configuration:

Created a VirtualHost configuration file (/etc/apache2/sites-available/your_project_name.conf) to define the server's behavior for this specific project.
Configured the VirtualHost with appropriate directives, including the DocumentRoot path and AllowOverride settings.
Enabled the new VirtualHost configuration using a2ensite your_project_name.conf.
Disabled the default Apache site (a2dissite 000-default.conf) to avoid conflicts.
Restarted the Apache service (systemctl restart apache2) to apply the configuration changes.
